<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-18T02:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-18T02:25:00-05:00" n="655" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/81: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-18T10:00:00+02:35">December 18, 1934—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 12:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>26. My telegram No. 25.<note n="21" xml:id="d655fn21">Not
                                    printed.</note> Revolt among Ethiopian desert Somalia rumored.
                                Owing to poor communications secrecy it is impossible to verify
                                rumored internal disorders. I am informed Emperor is considering
                                asking American mediation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>